    "synopsis": "Two years after the orks of the warlord Snagrod nearly annihilated the Crimson Fists, Chapter Master Pedro Kantor leads his rebuilt but still-depleted brethren in the grinding work of reclaiming Rynn's World. When an expedition from New Rynn City goes missing, Kantor marches to find them and walks into a carefully laid ambush at a place called Traitor's Gorge. Outmaneuvered and outnumbered, the Crimson Fists face destruction until aid arrives from the most unexpected of quarters. A tense battle-piece about a proud Chapter clawing back its strength and purpose, and the hard bargains survival sometimes demands.",
